		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message27465291">A clear cut choice for me, as this is simply a continuation of a series that I disliked even in my youthful days during my second full month of watching anime.<br />
<br />
Infinite Stratos 2.<br />
<br />
Even when my brain was naive and puny when I first started out, I still gave the original series a four, immediately after giving Kamisama no Memo-chou a nine. The seventeenth anime I've ever seen, the original Infinite Stratos was where I first started to develop a disdain for harems. Because of this, watching the second season may have been more for my own nostalgic purposes above giving it a fair, fresh shot at not being awful. Regardless, it ended up being awful, so I rated it as such. All of the characters are written with the fans in mind. The plot is laughably lazy. The animation is no better from the original (which had spotty CGI). Everything about is pretty much the bottom of the barrel. The only reason it was saved from a one was because of personal enjoyment. Laughing at its flaws. You all understand.<br />
<br />
Honorable Mentions:<br />
<br />
Freezing Vibration<br />
Kamisama no Nichiyoubi<br />
Watamote</div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><em>As long as I've got Henne, I've got a pretty penny.</em></div></td>
