		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message27542165">I could go with something like Valvrave, Infinite Stratos 2, Aku no Hana, Attack on Titan, OreImo 2, Kotoura-San, Devil Survivor 2...there's a lot I can choose from, but I'm ultimately tied between two of them.<br />
<br />
Blazblue: Alter Memory is probably the worst kind of TV adaptation of a video game. Reducing certain characters to roles so minor that they may as well not appear at all, horrible animation in a series that is all about the action and they even have the audacity to hint at a possible sequel. Blazblue's story-line is below average at best, and the constant time-loops and multiple endings make it difficult to animate, but this is just a really terrible way of adapting it. Carl appeared for about two minutes. Arakune was in for 10 seconds. The worst part is that George XIII (literally the only good thing about Rachel at all) didn't even make an appearance! For shame! The one redeeming feature is that the music is still intact, hearing Lust SIN in an anime was pretty cool, but even that doesn't change how terrible this is.<br />
<br />
It's either that or the second Code Geass OVA, which has practically killed any chance of this being an enjoyably bad OVA and changed it to just really terrible with totally implausible mechs (one of them is a centaur) and a horrible cast. Blazblue probably beats it out for worst anime of the year, but it's only by a small margin.</div><div style="margin-top: 8px;"><em>Modified by Masserati_, 01-08-14, 4:56 AM</em></div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
