		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message27666979">I'm going to agree with NavyCherub, though I'll admit my experience isn't as in-depth, seeing as I didn't start watching airing anime until Fall season. But Sekai de Ichiban Tsuyoku Naratai was really, really quite bad. <br />
<br />
The fanservice I expected. The fifteen minutes per episode of the main character crying in pain while other characters watch and grimace and eventually give up on watching the live show in a show- didn't anticipate that. It got to the point where I was embarrassed to tell people I was watching it. Yes, I picked this up in the off chance it would be good. Please don't judge me. It's one of few 1/10s. I won't even be giving BlazBlue such a low rating, and that's getting some extra hate-rating for dragging the BlazBlue name through the mud.</div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><span style="font-size: 80%;"><div style="text-align: center;"><img class="userimg" data-src="http://fc06.deviantart.net/fs42/f/2009/096/7/8/Tonberry_Banner_by_Doaj.jpg" /><br />
